.Dd December 11, 2006
.Dt LDEXP 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm ldexp
.Nd multiply by integer power of 2
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Fd #include <math.h>
.Ft double
.Fn ldexp "double x" "int n"
.Ft long double
.Fn ldexpl "long double x" "int n"
.Ft float
.Fn ldexpf "float x" "int n"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn ldexp
functions multiply x by 2 to the power n.
.Sh SPECIAL VALUES
.Fn ldexp "±0" "n"
returns ±0.
.Pp
.Fn ldexp "x" "0"
returns x.
.Pp
.Fn ldexp "±infinity" "n"
returns ±infinity.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr math 3 ,
.Xr scalbn 3 
.Sh STANDARDS
The
.Fn ldexp
functions conform to ISO/IEC 9899:2011.
